	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St. Thomas</placeName> <date>30 Dec 1849</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My Dr Sir</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)">I have not had this pleasure for some time<lb/> not having any thing of great importance to communicate<lb/>  I recd your introductory letter for <persName>Rabbi Cohen</persName> &#38; paid him<lb/> attention I collected &#36;154 for him he left for <placeName>Curacao</placeName> 15<lb/> days ago.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">It was with much <del>regret</del> pain I read your letter of <date>29 Oct</date><lb/> stating that in consequence of the differences with yourself &#38;<lb/> congregation it was not unlikely that you would give up<lb/> your situation as minister.  I hope that your anticipations<lb/> will not be realized &#38; that you may for many years continue<lb/> your duties.  I regret to join you in opinion that the greater<lb/> portion of our people lack in respect to their ministers &#38;<lb/> require them to be the tail instead of heads of Congregations&#44;<lb/> this feeling &#38; the <sic>apparant</sic> non&#45;desire for religious Instruction&#44;<lb/> added to the disinclination of contributing a few dollars<lb/> prevents our having a minister.  I confess that I am tired of<lb/> exertion in this cause my return has been&#44; &#38; is&#44; <hi rend="underline">Enemies</hi> the<lb/> only chance that a portion of our young people have of<lb/> religious instruction is what my very feeble abilities can<lb/> impart to them thro&#39; the Sunday School&#44; &#38; even this altho&#39;<lb/> gratuitous I can with difficulty keep together&#44; I am<lb/> however determined to keep it up so long as the Almighty<lb/> spares me health&#59; even the leaches have fallen off &#38; my Wife<lb/> &#38; self are the only ones who keep it on&#44; God may in his<lb/> mercy bring us a change.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed I forward you a pact of Hymns used in<lb/> the Sunday School which I wish you to have printed in<lb/> pamphlets of equal sized leaves neatly done.  I require Two<lb/> hundred with covers&#44;The following Hymns composed by <persName>Mr.</persName></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><persName>Mr Carillon</persName> I wish his name attached to</p>
				<p>N 1 Introductory Hymn</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;2 Halel</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;3 ditto&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;with the written alterations</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;4 ditto</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;6 choir No1</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;7 do&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;2 with the word &#8220;both&#8221; inscribed in the<lb/> second verse 1 Line as noted</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;8 En Kelihener</p>
				<p>&#160;&#160;9 Forward to Jerusalem</p>
				<p> the following after</p>
				<p>O &#8220;God to thee my voice I raise&#59; &#40;by a Young Lady at <placeName>Richmond</placeName>.</p>
				<p>Paraphrase of the Hebrew Creed&#44;</p>
				<p rend="align(right)">from the Jewish Chronicle</p>
				<p><date>Sabbath&#45;Eve</date> Hymn</p>
				<p>Costly&#8212;Conclusive Hymn from <persName>Revd DeSola&#39;s</persName><lb/> prayer Book.</p>
				<p>I leave the arrangement of the Frontspiece to you.<lb/>  I would like it to run thus</p>
				<p>&#8220;Hymns&#8221; composed by the <persName>Revd B C Carillon</persName> for the use<lb/> of the <placeName>St Thomas</placeName> Israelite Sunday School&#44; as well as<lb/> others selected for the same purpose by <persName role="author">A Wolff</persName><lb/> Founder &#38; Instructor</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">The <hi rend="underline">School opened in</hi> the month of <date>April 1842</date><lb/> Let me ask you to improve the above if you think it<lb/> necessary.  I require 2 dozen of <persName><sic>Picke&#39;s</sic></persName> Catechisms for<lb/> infants please forward them with as little delay as<lb/> possible</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I suppose that <persName>Mr Nathan</persName> Must be now in<lb/> <placeName>New Orleans</placeName> I hear that he is to be minister there</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">My wife joins with best regards&#44; &#38; I am</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Yours Truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">A. Wolff</persName></p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p><addressee>Revd. Mr. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
